## 編碼規範
<!-- Generic standards from templates/workflow-rules/coding-standards.md -->
<!-- Override in this file if project needs different conventions -->

### Core Principles
- **Simplicity First**: Minimal code impact, avoid over-engineering
- **No Temporary Fixes**: Find root causes, no "TODO: fix later"
- **Senior Developer Standards**: Production-ready code, not prototype quality

### Naming Conventions
- Files: `PascalCase.tsx` (components), `camelCase.ts` (utils), `kebab-case.sh` (scripts)
- Variables: `camelCase`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Booleans: Prefix with `is`, `has`, `should`, `can`

### TypeScript (if applicable)
- Strict mode enabled
- Explicit return types for public functions
- No `any` except for gradual migration or truly dynamic data
- Prefer `unknown` over `any` when type is uncertain

### Error Handling
- ALWAYS wrap async operations in try-catch
- User-facing errors: Show helpful message
- Developer errors: Log details to console
- Never silently catch errors

### Functions
- Max 50 lines for most functions
- Max 3 parameters (use object for more)
- Single responsibility principle
- Descriptive names that explain what they do

